<body>
    <h1>FoodDash – Online Food Delivery Platform</h1>
    <p>FoodDash is a comprehensive, full-stack food delivery ecosystem designed to facilitate seamless interactions between customers, restaurants, and delivery personnel. The system utilizes modern mobile and web technologies to provide a real-time, efficient delivery experience.</p>

    <h2>🏗️ System Architecture</h2>
    <p>The platform follows a centralized backend architecture. A single PHP REST API serves as the communication hub for all four primary interfaces:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Customer App:</strong> Flutter-based mobile application.</li>
        <li><strong>Restaurant App:</strong> Flutter-based mobile application.</li>
        <li><strong>Delivery App:</strong> Flutter-based mobile application.</li>
        <li><strong>Admin Panel:</strong> PHP & Bootstrap 5 web interface.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>📱 Core Applications</h2>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Application</th>
                <th>Technology</th>
                <th>Primary Function</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td class="role-customer">Customer App</td>
                <td>Flutter</td>
                <td>Browse menus, place orders, and track deliveries in real-time.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="role-restaurant">Restaurant App</td>
                <td>Flutter</td>
                <td>Manage order incoming requests, menu items, and earnings.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="role-delivery">Delivery App</td>
                <td>Flutter</td>
                <td>Accept delivery tasks, navigate to locations, and verify deliveries via OTP.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Admin Panel</td>
                <td>PHP / JS</td>
                <td>Oversee users, restaurants, coupons, and system-wide analytics.</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>🔐 Security & Authentication</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>JWT (JSON Web Tokens):</strong> Used for secure, stateless communication between the mobile apps and the API.</li>
        <li><strong>BCrypt Hashing:</strong> All user passwords are encrypted using industry-standard BCrypt.</li>
        <li><strong>Role-Based Access:</strong> Strict permission levels ensure users can only access data relevant to their role.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>📦 Backend Infrastructure</h2>
    <p>The backend is located in the <code>/backend</code> directory and is built using high-performance Vanilla PHP.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Database:</strong> MySQL (relational database management).</li>
        <li><strong>Push Notifications:</strong> Integrated with Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM).</li>
        <li><strong>Real-time Tracking:</strong> Geolocation updates processed via specialized tracking controllers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>🔄 The Order Life Cycle</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Selection:</strong> The Customer selects items and applies coupons in the Customer App.</li>
        <li><strong>Confirmation:</strong> The Restaurant receives the order and starts preparation.</li>
        <li><strong>Assignment:</strong> A Delivery Boy is notified of a new pickup request.</li>
        <li><strong>Movement:</strong> The Delivery Boy picks up the order and tracks their progress via GPS.</li>
        <li><strong>Completion:</strong> The Customer provides an OTP to the Delivery Boy to confirm receipt.</li>
    </ol>

    <p><br><em>Generated by Antigravity AI for FoodDash Project Documentation.</em></p>
